---
Remove leftover items pertaining to the deprecated inode cache feature

For every fs tree (the default subvolume and every user subvolume), walks the
items keyed under `BTRFS_FREE_INO_OBJECTID` (and historically also
`BTRFS_FREE_SPACE_OBJECTID`, which old kernels used for the per-inode cache
bitmap), drops every referenced data extent via the delayed-ref queue, and
deletes the items themselves. The transaction crate's data-ref drop path also
trims the csum tree for any fully-freed extent.

The device must not be mounted.

Usage: clear-ino-cache <DEVICE>

Arguments:
  <DEVICE>
          Path to the btrfs device

Options:
  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
